# Vercel Speed Insights Implementation

## Summary
Successfully installed and configured Vercel Speed Insights for this Next.js project following the latest official documentation from Vercel.

## Changes Made

### 1. Package Installation
- **File**: `package.json`
- **Change**: Added `@vercel/speed-insights` version `^2.0.0` as a dependency
- **Method**: Installed using `npm install @vercel/speed-insights`

### 2. Layout Configuration
- **File**: `src/app/layout.tsx`
- **Changes**:
  - Added import: `import { SpeedInsights } from "@vercel/speed-insights/next"`
  - Added `<SpeedInsights />` component in the RootLayout body, positioned after the existing `<Analytics />` component

### 3. Lock File Update
- **File**: `package-lock.json`
- **Change**: Updated to reflect the new dependency and its sub-dependencies

## Implementation Details

Following the official Vercel Speed Insights quickstart guide for Next.js App Router:
- Fetched the latest documentation from https://vercel.com/docs/speed-insights/quickstart
- Used the Next.js-specific import path (`@vercel/speed-insights/next`)
- Placed the component in the root layout file for site-wide tracking
- Positioned the component at the end of the body, following the same pattern as the existing Analytics component

## Testing & Verification

✅ **Build Test**: Successfully built the project using `npm run build`
- No TypeScript errors
- All pages compiled successfully (7 routes generated)
- Build completed in 6.3 seconds

✅ **Code Quality**: 
- TypeScript compilation passed with no errors
- No linting scripts available in project (none were broken)
- No test scripts available in project

## Next Steps

To complete the Speed Insights setup:
1. Deploy the changes to Vercel
2. Enable Speed Insights in the Vercel dashboard (Project → Speed Insights → Enable)
3. After deployment, the tracking will begin collecting data
4. Performance metrics will be available in the Speed Insights dashboard within a few days

## Notes

- The project already had Vercel Analytics installed, and Speed Insights follows the same integration pattern
- The implementation is framework-specific for Next.js App Router, ensuring optimal performance
- No additional configuration or environment variables are required
